verses.text_plain: Praise ye the Lord. Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise in the congregation of saints.
verses.verse_html:
1Praise ye the Lord. Sing unto the Lord a new song, and his praise in the congregation of saints. ▼
▼ Praise…: Heb. Hallelujah

verses.text_plain: Let Israel rejoice in him that made him: let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.
verses.verse_html:
2Let Israel rejoice in him that made him: let the children of Zion be joyful in their King. ▼
▼ in him…: Heb. in his Makers

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in him…: Heb. in his Makers
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in him…: Heb. in his Makers

verses.text_plain: Let them praise his name in the dance: let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp.
verses.verse_html:
3Let them praise his name in the dance: let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp. ▼
▼ in…: or, with the pipe

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in…: or, with the pipe

verses.text_plain: For the Lord taketh pleasure in his people: he will beautify the meek with salvation.
verses.verse_html: 4For the Lord taketh pleasure in his people: he will beautify the meek with salvation.

verses.text_plain: Let the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.
verses.verse_html: 5Let the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.

verses.text_plain: Let the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand;
verses.verse_html:
6Let the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a twoedged sword in their hand; ▼
▼ mouth: Heb. throat

verses.text_plain: To execute vengeance upon the heathen, and punishments upon the people;
verses.verse_html: 7To execute vengeance upon the heathen, and punishments upon the people;

verses.text_plain: To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron;
verses.verse_html: 8To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron;

verses.text_plain: To execute upon them the judgment written: this honour have all his saints. Praise ye the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 9To execute upon them the judgment written: this honour have all his saints. Praise ye the Lord.
